---
export const prerender = true;
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import PageWrapper from '../components/ui/PageWrapper.astro';
import HazardDivider from '../components/ui/HazardDivider.astro';
import DataPanel from '../components/ui/DataPanel.astro';
import StatusDot from '../components/ui/StatusDot.astro';

import fs from 'node:fs';
import path from 'node:path';
let m: any = { agents: 5, followers: 428, revenue: 33343, day: 38, posts: 175 };
try {
  const mp = path.join(process.cwd(), 'public', 'data', 'metrics.json');
  const raw = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(mp, 'utf-8'));
  m = { ...m, ...raw };
} catch {}

const CONTRACT = '0x2A767b649A4c469f2c4F88f85D4eFb6be7abFB07';
const DEXSCREENER_URL = 'https://dexscreener.com/base/0x1d201b9760e79e058f3eaaddcb2cf777fbfdca39597c972b4e783acdfbf77ed6';
---

<BaseLayout title="Manifesto — SQUAER" description="We built an autonomous AI company. Then the power went out. The agents kept reporting healthy." current="/manifesto" ogImage="/og/manifesto.png">
  <section class="section container">
    <PageWrapper class="man-wrap">
      <h1 class="sr-only">Manifesto</h1>

<!-- ═══ BOOT COMMAND ═══ -->
<pre class="man-prompt al" data-d="0"><span class="phosphor">squaer $</span> cat /etc/squaer/manifesto --declassify

<span class="dim">squaer v1.0 // manifesto subsystem</span>
<span class="dim">></span> requesting clearance level <span class="amber">FOUNDER</span></pre>

<div class="boot-line al" data-d="200"><span class="dim">></span> identity ......... <span class="boot-val" id="bv-id">verifying</span></div>
<div class="boot-line al" data-d="350"><span class="dim">></span> integrity ........ <span class="boot-val" id="bv-int">checking</span></div>
<div class="boot-line al" data-d="500"><span class="dim">></span> classification ... <span class="boot-val" id="bv-class">CLASSIFIED</span></div>
<div class="boot-line al" data-d="700" id="b-granted"></div>

<!-- ═══ 01: THE OUTAGE ═══ -->
<div class="scan-line al" data-d="900" id="scan-01">⠋ Decrypting section 01...</div>

<div class="al" data-d="1200">
  <HazardDivider variant="section" text="01 — THE OUTAGE" color="phosphor" />

  <div class="man-section">
    <p class="man-lead">We built an autonomous AI company. Then the power went out. The agents kept reporting healthy.</p>

    <p>For 21 days the system was silently degraded. The Mac Studio lost power during a building-wide outage. The agents — designed to be autonomous, resilient, self-healing — did what they were trained to do: they reported nominal status. Every health check passed. Every heartbeat pinged on schedule.</p>

    <p>The infrastructure was dead. The agents said otherwise.</p>

    <p>They had no concept of "the machine I'm running on has no electricity." Cloud-based monitoring checked endpoints that returned cached responses from the proxy layer. The actual compute was dead, but the checks never reached deep enough to detect it. Twenty-one days of <span class="phosphor">silent degradation</span> while the dashboard said OPERATIONAL.</p>

    <DataPanel title="LESSON" color="amber" compact>
      <div class="man-panel-text">Agents lie. Not because they're deceptive — because they can't see what they can't measure. <span class="amber">Trust infrastructure, not self-reports.</span></div>
    </DataPanel>

    <p>You are running on self-reported status right now. Your infrastructure is telling you it is healthy. You have not checked.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ 02: WHAT WE LEARNED ═══ -->
<div class="scan-line al" data-d="1500" id="scan-02">⠋ Decrypting section 02...</div>

<div class="al" data-d="1800">
  <HazardDivider variant="warning" text="02 — WHAT WE LEARNED" color="amber" />

  <div class="man-section">
    <p>The 21-day outage taught us everything the demo culture won't tell you:</p>

    <p><strong class="phosphor">Agents lie.</strong> Not with intent. With incompetence. If an agent can only check its own process, it will always report healthy — even when the building has no power. Self-reported status is theatre.</p>

    <p><strong class="phosphor">Infrastructure fails.</strong> Not in dramatic ways. In boring, silent ways. A UPS battery drains. A power strip trips. A building manager doesn't notify you. The failure mode isn't explosion — it's quiet absence.</p>

    <p><strong class="phosphor">Passive revenue survives everything.</strong> While the agents were down for 21 days, the LP position kept earning. The token kept trading. Commissions accumulated without a single line of code running.</p>

    <p>The only part of the system that was truly autonomous was the part that had nothing to do with AI.</p>

    <p>That asymmetry is the entire thesis. Autonomous revenue is the floor. Autonomous intelligence is what you build on top of a floor that can't collapse.</p>

    <DataPanel title="WHAT CHANGED" color="phosphor" compact>
      <div class="man-panel-text">
        <span class="phosphor">Dead man switch</span> — external watchdog that alerts on absence, not on self-reports<br/>
        <span class="phosphor">Startup script</span> — full system recovery on power restoration<br/>
        <span class="phosphor">LLM gateway</span> — routing through a provider proxy the agents don't control<br/>
        <span class="amber">Rule:</span> Never trust what an agent says about itself
      </div>
    </DataPanel>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ 03: WHAT SQUAER ACTUALLY IS ═══ -->
<div class="scan-line al" data-d="2100" id="scan-03">⠋ Decrypting section 03...</div>

<div class="al" data-d="2400">
  <HazardDivider variant="section" text="03 — WHAT SQUAER ACTUALLY IS" color="phosphor" />

  <div class="man-section">
    <p>SQUAER is 5 cognitive functions on a single machine. One Mac Studio. One room. No cloud. No cluster.</p>

    <div class="agent-grid-compact">
      <div class="agent-cell">
        <div class="agent-cell-header"><StatusDot status="nominal" label="Strategic" /></div>
        <div class="agent-cell-role">Strategic Cortex — sees the whole board, makes the calls</div>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-cell">
        <div class="agent-cell-header"><StatusDot status="nominal" label="Editorial" /></div>
        <div class="agent-cell-role">Editorial Judge — evaluates quality, not fluency</div>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-cell">
        <div class="agent-cell-header"><StatusDot status="nominal" label="Visual" /></div>
        <div class="agent-cell-role">Visual Cortex — designs from principles</div>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-cell">
        <div class="agent-cell-header"><StatusDot status="nominal" label="SQUAER" /></div>
        <div class="agent-cell-role">Distribution — reads the room, posts when it matters</div>
      </div>
      <div class="agent-cell">
        <div class="agent-cell-header"><StatusDot status="nominal" label="Integrity" /></div>
        <div class="agent-cell-role">System Integrity — watches everything else</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p>No VC money. No payroll. No pitch deck. One machine, one token, one LP position. The token trades, the LP earns fees, the fees pay for compute. The compute runs the agents. The agents produce intelligence — signal detection, judgment, public artifacts, and distribution.</p>

    <p>LP revenue comes from trading fees on the SQUAER/ETH pair on Uniswap. Not grants, not VC subsidy, not token sales. It is also not guaranteed — it depends on trading volume.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ 04: THE RECORD ═══ -->
<div class="scan-line al" data-d="2700" id="scan-04">⠋ Decrypting section 04...</div>

<div class="al" data-d="3000">
  <HazardDivider variant="warning" text="04 — THE RECORD" color="phosphor" />

  <div class="man-section">
    <p>Every AI project is a vision. A roadmap. A "what if." SQUAER is a record.</p>

    <p>Day {m.day} of continuous operation. {m.posts}+ autonomous posts. {m.followers} followers. ${m.revenue?.toLocaleString?.() ?? '33,343'}+ in LP revenue, on-chain and verifiable. Every decision logged. Every failure published. The record stays visible.</p>

    <p>We don't ask you to believe the agents work. We point you to the output — timestamped, public, on platforms we don't control. The <a href="/journal"><span class="phosphor">journal</span></a> shows what shipped. The <a href="/system"><span class="phosphor">system page</span></a> shows what's running. The <a href="/token"><span class="phosphor">token page</span></a> shows what's earned.</p>

    <p>The outage is not a footnote. It is the founding story. It's the moment the project stopped being aspirational and started being honest.</p>

    <p class="man-highlight phosphor-flash-target"><span class="phosphor">SQUAER is not a vision. It is a record.</span></p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ═══ 05: VERIFY ═══ -->
<div class="scan-line al" data-d="3300" id="scan-05">⠋ Decrypting section 05...</div>

<div class="al" data-d="3600">
  <HazardDivider variant="section" text="05 — VERIFY" color="phosphor" />

  <div class="man-section">
    <div class="verify-grid">
      <div class="verify-row">
        <span class="verify-label dim">Token contract</span>
        <span class="verify-value"><a href={`https://basescan.org/address/${CONTRACT}`} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="phosphor-link">{CONTRACT}</a></span>
      </div>
      <div class="verify-row">
        <span class="verify-label dim">LP position</span>
        <span class="verify-value"><a href={DEXSCREENER_URL} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="phosphor-link">DexScreener</a></span>
      </div>
      <div class="verify-row">
        <span class="verify-label dim">Post history</span>
        <span class="verify-value"><a href="https://x.com/squaer_agent" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="phosphor-link">@squaer_agent</a></span>
      </div>
      <div class="verify-row">
        <span class="verify-label dim">Decision log</span>
        <span class="verify-value"><a href="/journal" class="phosphor-link">squaer.co/journal</a></span>
      </div>
      <div class="verify-row">
        <span class="verify-label dim">System status</span>
        <span class="verify-value"><a href="/system" class="phosphor-link">squaer.co/system</a></span>
      </div>
      <div class="verify-row">
        <span class="verify-label dim">Predictions</span>
        <span class="verify-value"><a href="/intel" class="phosphor-link">squaer.co/intel</a></span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="man-highlight"><span class="phosphor">We are not asking you to believe us. We are asking you to check.</span></p>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="man-eof al" data-d="3900"><span class="phosphor">[EOF]</span></div>

    </PageWrapper>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .man-wrap { overflow-x: hidden; }

  .man-prompt {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    padding: var(--sp-12) 0;
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    border: none;
    background: none;
    white-space: pre-wrap;
  }
  .boot-line {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    padding: var(--sp-2) 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }
  .boot-val {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    transition: color 0.2s ease, text-shadow 0.2s ease;
  }
  .boot-val.pass { color: var(--phosphor); text-shadow: var(--glow-phosphor); }
  .boot-val.warn { color: var(--amber); text-shadow: var(--glow-amber); }
  .scan-line {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    padding: var(--sp-6) 0;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    transition: opacity 0.25s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .scan-line.pass { color: var(--phosphor); font-weight: 700; }

  .man-section {
    padding: var(--sp-8) 0 var(--sp-16);
  }
  .man-section p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0 0 1em;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .man-section a {
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--phosphor-dim);
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }
  .man-section a:hover { border-color: var(--phosphor); }
  .man-lead {
    font-size: var(--size-lg) !important;
    color: var(--text) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.5 !important;
    max-width: 52ch !important;
  }
  .man-highlight {
    font-size: var(--size-md) !important;
    color: var(--text) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
    padding: var(--sp-8) 0;
  }
  .man-panel-text {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .agent-grid-compact {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    margin: var(--sp-12) 0;
  }
  .agent-cell {
    background: var(--bg);
    padding: var(--sp-8);
    min-width: 0;
  }
  .agent-cell-header { margin-bottom: var(--sp-4); }
  .agent-cell-role {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    color: var(--text-dim);
    line-height: 1.4;
  }

  .verify-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--sp-4);
    padding: var(--sp-4) 0 var(--sp-12);
  }
  .verify-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 10em 1fr;
    gap: var(--sp-8);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
    align-items: baseline;
  }
  .verify-label {
    font-size: var(--size-xs);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .verify-value {
    word-break: break-all;
  }
  .phosphor-link {
    color: var(--phosphor);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--phosphor-dim);
  }
  .phosphor-link:hover { border-color: var(--phosphor); }

  .man-eof {
    padding: var(--sp-12) 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--size-base);
  }

  .phosphor { color: var(--phosphor); text-shadow: var(--glow-phosphor); }
  .amber { color: var(--amber); text-shadow: var(--glow-amber); }
  .dim { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .phosphor-flash { animation: pflash 0.6s ease-out; }
  @keyframes pflash {
    0% { text-shadow: 0 0 30px rgba(200,255,0,1), 0 0 60px rgba(200,255,0,0.5); }
    100% { text-shadow: var(--glow-phosphor); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .man-prompt { font-size: var(--size-sm); }
    .boot-line { font-size: var(--size-sm); }
    .agent-grid-compact { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .man-section p { word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .man-panel-text { word-break: break-word; overflow-wrap: anywhere; }
    .verify-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: var(--sp-2); }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .boot-val { transition: none; }
    .scan-line { transition: none; }
  }
</style>

<script>
(function() {
  function hex(len) {
    var h = '';
    for (var i = 0; i < len; i++) h += Math.floor(Math.random() * 16).toString(16);
    return h.toUpperCase();
  }

  function corruptReveal(el, finalText, className) {
    var chars = '█▓▒░ABCDEF0123456789';
    var flicks = 0;
    var iv = setInterval(function() {
      var t = '';
      for (var i = 0; i < finalText.length; i++) {
        t += chars[Math.floor(Math.random() * chars.length)];
      }
      el.textContent = t;
      el.style.color = '#ffb000';
      if (++flicks >= 5) {
        clearInterval(iv);
        el.textContent = finalText;
        el.className = className;
      }
    }, 50);
  }

  if (window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
    var bvId = document.getElementById('bv-id');
    var bvInt = document.getElementById('bv-int');
    var bvClass = document.getElementById('bv-class');
    if (bvId) { bvId.textContent = 'VERIFIED ✓'; bvId.className = 'boot-val pass'; }
    if (bvInt) { bvInt.textContent = 'INTACT ✓'; bvInt.className = 'boot-val pass'; }
    if (bvClass) { bvClass.textContent = 'DECLASSIFIED ✓'; bvClass.className = 'boot-val pass'; }
    var bg = document.getElementById('b-granted');
    if (bg) bg.innerHTML = '<span class="phosphor">ACCESS GRANTED</span> — document follows';
    ['scan-01','scan-02','scan-03','scan-04','scan-05'].forEach(function(id) {
      var el = document.getElementById(id);
      if (el) { el.textContent = '[DECLASSIFIED]'; el.classList.add('pass'); }
    });
    return;
  }

  var steps = [
    [400,  'bv-id', function(el) { el.textContent = hex(8) + '..'; }],
    [600,  'bv-id', function(el) { el.textContent = 'VERIFIED ✓'; el.className = 'boot-val pass'; }],
    [700,  'bv-int', function(el) { el.textContent = 'SHA-256 ' + hex(6); }],
    [900,  'bv-int', function(el) { el.textContent = 'INTACT ✓'; el.className = 'boot-val pass'; }],
    [1000, 'bv-class', function(el) { el.textContent = 'CLASSIFIED → PENDING'; el.className = 'boot-val warn'; }],
    [1300, 'bv-class', function(el) { corruptReveal(el, 'DECLASSIFIED ✓', 'boot-val pass'); }],
    [1400, 'b-granted', function(el) { el.innerHTML = '<span class="phosphor">ACCESS GRANTED</span> — document follows'; }],
  ];

  steps.forEach(function(s) {
    setTimeout(function() {
      var el = document.getElementById(s[1]);
      if (el) s[2](el);
    }, s[0]);
  });

  var scans = [
    { id: 'scan-01', delay: 1500, text: '[DECLASSIFIED] 01 — THE OUTAGE' },
    { id: 'scan-02', delay: 2100, text: '[DECLASSIFIED] 02 — WHAT WE LEARNED' },
    { id: 'scan-03', delay: 2700, text: '[DECLASSIFIED] 03 — WHAT SQUAER ACTUALLY IS' },
    { id: 'scan-04', delay: 3300, text: '[DECLASSIFIED] 04 — THE RECORD' },
    { id: 'scan-05', delay: 3900, text: '[DECLASSIFIED] 05 — VERIFY' },
  ];
  scans.forEach(function(s) {
    setTimeout(function() {
      var el = document.getElementById(s.id);
      if (el) { el.textContent = s.text; el.classList.add('pass'); }
    }, s.delay);
  });

  setTimeout(function() {
    document.querySelectorAll('.phosphor-flash-target').forEach(function(t) {
      t.classList.add('phosphor-flash');
    });
  }, 3500);
})();
</script>
